Add the `POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/tasks/:taskId/stop` endpoint to `apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts`. This endpoint delegates to `runtime.stopTask()` and returns structured JSON responses.

## Implementation

Add the following route to `apps/server/src/routes/sessions.ts`:

```typescript
// POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/tasks/:taskId/stop - Stop a background task
router.post('/:id/tasks/:taskId/stop', async (req, res) => {
  const sessionId = parseSessionId(req.params.id);
  if (!sessionId) return sendError(res, 400, 'Invalid session ID', 'INVALID_SESSION_ID');

  const { taskId } = req.params;
  if (!taskId) return sendError(res, 400, 'Task ID is required', 'MISSING_TASK_ID');

  const runtime = runtimeRegistry.getDefault();

  if (!runtime.hasSession(sessionId)) {
    return sendError(res, 404, 'Session not found', 'SESSION_NOT_FOUND');
  }

  try {
    const stopped = await runtime.stopTask(sessionId, taskId);
    if (!stopped) {
      return res.status(409).json({ error: 'Task already stopped or not found' });
    }
    res.json({ success: true, taskId });
  } catch (err) {
    logger.error('Failed to stop task %s in session %s: %O', taskId, sessionId, err);
    return sendError(res, 500, 'Failed to stop task', 'STOP_TASK_FAILED');
  }
});
```

This endpoint:
- Validates session ID and task ID from URL params
- Checks session exists via `runtime.hasSession()`
- Delegates to `runtime.stopTask()` which returns a boolean
- Returns 200 `{ success: true, taskId }` on success
- Returns 409 `{ error: 'Task already stopped or not found' }` if stop returns false
- Returns 404 if session not found
- Returns 500 with logged error on unexpected failure

## Acceptance Criteria
- `POST /api/sessions/:id/tasks/:taskId/stop` returns 200 with `{ success: true, taskId }` on success
- Returns 409 when task is already stopped or not found
- Returns 404 when session doesn't exist
- Returns 400 for invalid session ID
- Error cases are logged with appropriate context
- Route placement follows existing pattern in sessions.ts (thin handler, delegates to runtime)

Update `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/sdk-event-mapper.ts` to emit `background_task_started`, `background_task_progress`, and `background_task_done` SSE events instead of the old `subagent_*` events. Add type discrimination logic to distinguish agent tasks from bash tasks.

## Implementation

In `sdk-event-mapper.ts`, replace the three subagent handler blocks inside the `if (message.type === 'system' && 'subtype' in message)` section:

### Replace `task_started` handler:

```typescript
if (message.subtype === 'task_started') {
  const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;
  // Discrimination: presence of session_id field indicates a subagent (child session).
  // Absence means a bash command. Fallback: if session_id is the same as the parent,
  // treat as bash (self-reference, not a child).
  const taskSessionId = msg.session_id as string | undefined;
  const hasChildSession = taskSessionId && taskSessionId !== session.sdkSessionId;
  const taskType = hasChildSession ? 'agent' : 'bash';

  yield {
    type: 'background_task_started',
    data: {
      taskId: msg.task_id as string,
      taskType,
      startedAt: Date.now(),
      // Agent-specific
      ...(taskType === 'agent'
        ? {
            subagentSessionId: taskSessionId,
            toolUseId: msg.tool_use_id as string | undefined,
            description: msg.description as string,
          }
        : {
            command: (msg.description as string) || (msg.command as string) || 'Background task',
          }),
    },
  };
  return;
}
```

### Replace `task_progress` handler:

```typescript
if (message.subtype === 'task_progress') {
  const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;
  const usage = msg.usage as { tool_uses: number; duration_ms: number };
  yield {
    type: 'background_task_progress',
    data: {
      taskId: msg.task_id as string,
      toolUses: usage.tool_uses,
      lastToolName: msg.last_tool_name as string | undefined,
      durationMs: usage.duration_ms,
    },
  };
  return;
}
```

### Replace `task_notification` handler:

```typescript
if (message.subtype === 'task_notification') {
  const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;
  const usage = msg.usage as { tool_uses: number; duration_ms: number } | undefined;
  yield {
    type: 'background_task_done',
    data: {
      taskId: msg.task_id as string,
      status: msg.status as 'completed' | 'failed' | 'stopped',
      summary: msg.summary as string | undefined,
      toolUses: usage?.tool_uses,
      durationMs: usage?.duration_ms,
    },
  };
  return;
}
```

The key discrimination logic:
- `task_started` SDK messages with a `session_id` that differs from the parent session's `sdkSessionId` are typed as `'agent'`
- All others default to `'bash'`
- This must be validated against real SDK payloads during implementation. If the SDK doesn't provide `session_id` on task_started, fall back to a heuristic: messages with a `description` matching agent patterns are `'agent'`, others are `'bash'`

## Acceptance Criteria
- `task_started` SDK messages emit `background_task_started` with correct `taskType` discrimination
- Agent tasks include `subagentSessionId`, `description`, `toolUseId`
- Bash tasks include `command`
- All events include `startedAt` timestamp
- `task_progress` emits `background_task_progress`
- `task_notification` emits `background_task_done`
- No references to `subagent_started`, `subagent_progress`, or `subagent_done` remain in this file

Implement the `stopTask` method on `ClaudeCodeRuntime` in `apps/server/src/services/runtimes/claude-code/`. This method delegates to the SDK's `query.stopTask()` method.

## Implementation

Locate the `ClaudeCodeRuntime` class (likely in `claude-code-runtime.ts`) and add the `stopTask` method:

```typescript
async stopTask(sessionId: string, taskId: string): Promise<boolean> {
  const session = this.sessions.get(sessionId);
  if (!session?.query) {
    logger.warn('stopTask: no active query for session %s', sessionId);
    return false;
  }

  try {
    await session.query.stopTask(taskId);
    return true;
  } catch (err) {
    logger.error('stopTask failed for task %s in session %s: %O', taskId, sessionId, err);
    return false;
  }
}
```

Key implementation notes:
- The `session.query` object is the active SDK query instance for the session
- `query.stopTask(taskId)` is provided by the Claude Agent SDK
- If the session has no active query (idle session), return false
- Catch and log errors but don't throw — the route handler uses the boolean return to determine the HTTP status code
- Race condition: if the task completes between the user clicking stop and this call executing, the SDK stopTask is a no-op. The completion notification will have already flowed through SSE.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `stopTask(sessionId, taskId)` returns `true` when SDK `query.stopTask()` succeeds
- Returns `false` when session doesn't exist or has no active query
- Returns `false` (not throws) on SDK errors
- Errors are logged with session and task context
- Method satisfies the `AgentRuntime.stopTask` interface contract

Rename and update the subagent handler functions in `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/stream-tool-handlers.ts` to handle `background_task_*` events with `BackgroundTaskPart`.

## Implementation

### 1. Update imports in `stream-tool-handlers.ts`

Replace:
```typescript
import type {
  SubagentStartedEvent,
  SubagentProgressEvent,
  SubagentDoneEvent,
} from '@dorkos/shared/types';
```

With:
```typescript
import type {
  BackgroundTaskStartedEvent,
  BackgroundTaskProgressEvent,
  BackgroundTaskDoneEvent,
} from '@dorkos/shared/types';
```

### 2. Replace handler functions

Replace `handleSubagentStarted`:
```typescript
/** Handle a background task being started (agent or bash). */
export function handleBackgroundTaskStarted(
  helpers: StreamHandlerHelpers,
  data: unknown,
  assistantId: string
) {
  const event = data as BackgroundTaskStartedEvent;
  helpers.currentPartsRef.current.push({
    type: 'background_task',
    taskId: event.taskId,
    taskType: event.taskType,
    status: 'running',
    startedAt: event.startedAt,
    description: event.description,
    command: event.command,
  });
  helpers.updateAssistantMessage(assistantId);
}
```

Replace `handleSubagentProgress`:
```typescript
/** Handle background task progress updates. */
export function handleBackgroundTaskProgress(
  helpers: StreamHandlerHelpers,
  data: unknown,
  assistantId: string
) {
  const progress = data as BackgroundTaskProgressEvent;
  const part = helpers.findBackgroundTask(progress.taskId);
  if (part) {
    if (progress.toolUses !== undefined) part.toolUses = progress.toolUses;
    part.lastToolName = progress.lastToolName;
    part.durationMs = progress.durationMs;
  } else {
    console.warn('[stream] background_task_progress: unknown taskId', progress.taskId);
  }
  helpers.updateAssistantMessage(assistantId);
}
```

Replace `handleSubagentDone`:
```typescript
/** Handle a background task completing. */
export function handleBackgroundTaskDone(
  helpers: StreamHandlerHelpers,
  data: unknown,
  assistantId: string
) {
  const done = data as BackgroundTaskDoneEvent;
  const part = helpers.findBackgroundTask(done.taskId);
  if (part) {
    part.status = done.status === 'completed' ? 'complete' : done.status === 'stopped' ? 'stopped' : 'error';
    part.summary = done.summary;
    if (done.toolUses !== undefined) part.toolUses = done.toolUses;
    if (done.durationMs !== undefined) part.durationMs = done.durationMs;
  } else {
    console.warn('[stream] background_task_done: unknown taskId', done.taskId);
  }
  helpers.updateAssistantMessage(assistantId);
}
```

Note the `handleBackgroundTaskDone` now maps `'stopped'` to `'stopped'` status (not `'error'`), since the new schema has a distinct `'stopped'` status.

